  "title": "Mechanical Assistant Manager [SL]",
  "description": "<p><ul><li>Demonstrate effective site problem-solving and coordination skills to clients.</li><li>Apply strong engineering expertise, particularly in design and compliance with building services codes of practice.</li><li>Ensure the quality of materials and installations by suppliers and subcontractors in accordance with the ISO quality plan.</li><li>Coordinate, monitor, and control suppliers’ materials, equipment, and subcontractor installation quality.</li><li>Prepare shop drawings and manage drawing coordination.</li><li>Develop work schedules and attend client and internal meetings.</li><li>Assist the Manager in daily site operations in line with master planning, quality, and safety requirements.</li><li>Coordinate closely with the main contractor to prevent rework.</li><li>Control site materials and equipment to minimize wastage.</li><li>Maintain close communication with suppliers and subcontractors to reduce delivery delays affecting progress.</li><li>Inspect materials and installations to identify and prevent non-conformance and defects.</li><li>Explore new technologies and installation methods to improve productivity.</li><li>Monitor site progress closely and communicate clearly with suppliers and subcontractors.</li></ul><p>Requirements</p></p><ul><li>Diploma in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Preferable 3-8 years’ relevant experience.</li></ul><p><br />We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p><p>EA License No: 20C0270</p><p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
